Step 1:

Goto www.getcomposer.org website to install composer. 

Click on Download.

Download and run Composer-Setup.exe

Install the composer.

After installation, to verify if it is installed go to command prompt and run command "composer -V" to check the version of composer. Here in -V the letter V is capital.

Woww... Composer is available now.

Step 2:

Now after installing composer we are going to setup laravel.

Type following command to get laravel installer.

composer global require "laravel/installer"

After it.. you can create a laravel project using below mentioned command.





